===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{lb|en|education}} The body of students corresponding to a particular grade level or year of study.
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1992|author=Charles C. Ragin, Howard Saul Becker|title=What Is a Case?: Exploring the Foundations of Social Inquiry|passage=Social units intermediate in size between the individual and the whole school are discussed. These units are the '''year-groups''', seen as developing collective perspectives which follow from the interaction between students' initial perspectives and their shared experiences, and the fraternities which were seen to structure daily social interaction.}}
#* {{quote-text|en|year=2016|author=J. Kathleen Cheney|title=Dreaming Death|page=255|passage=Some '''yeargroups''' broke down into cliques, usually dividing between the two primary training groups: hand-to-hand combat versus the marksmen.}}
